<subSubSection id="C6878F80462BFFE0FF4FFE56FB8AFD84" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8E22DC0B462BFFE0FF4FFE56FB8AFD84" blockId="6.[136,1451,445,613]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FF4FFE56FF67FE38" bold="true" box="[136,201,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="BCE90019462BFFE0FF16FE56FF44FE37" box="[209,234,446,471]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EA0CA1FA462BFFE0FF2DFE55FE28FE38" author="Kanitz, A." box="[234,390,445,472]" editor="Martius, C. F. P. von" firstAuthor="Kanitz" journalOrPublisher="Frid. Fleischer, Leipzig" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="130 - 187" refId="ref7111" refString="Kanitz, A. (1878) Lobeliaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P. von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 6 (4). Frid. Fleischer, Leipzig, pp. 130 - 187." title="Lobeliaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 6 (4)" year="1878">Kanitz (1878)</bibRefCitation>
referred in the protologue to a collection of Saint-Hillaire, without indication of the collection number. We found three duplicates from the collection c1-54 of Saint-Hillaire at P, with labels in Kanitz’s hand, suggesting that they were analyzed by him for the description of the species. The specimen number [P00714442] best fits the original description, and is the most complete among the three, containing a leaf at the base of the stem, leaf at the apex, bracts, and an inflorescence, and is thus designated here as the 
<typeStatus id="512662A9462BFFE0FC72FDA2FBB1FD84" box="[949,1055,586,612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
